posts.extended: This led to the development of a fan theory stating that machines don’t harvest humans for energy. Instead, they harvest humans for their consciousness and imagination. In a way, it makes sense that the machines would use people for their ability to learn and be creative. This, in turn, helps them to learn new skills to adapt and evolve.
